🎭 CONTEXT (ctx) API REFERENCE

📱 MESSAGE SENDING

1). **ctx.reply(text, options)

Purpose: Send a text message in reply to the current message

-code(
ctx.reply("Hello! 👋")
ctx.reply("Formatted text", parse_mode: 'Markdown')
ctx.reply("Secret message", disable_notification: true)
)

-note(Works in private chats, groups, and supergroups)

2). **ctx.edit_message_text(text, options)

Purpose: Edit an existing message's text

-code(

Edit the current message

ctx.edit_message_text("Updated content! ✏️")

Edit with formatting

ctx.edit_message_text("Bold update", parse_mode: 'MarkdownV2')
)

-warning(Only works for messages sent by your bot)

3). ctx.delete_message(message_id = nil)

Purpose: Delete a message from the chat

-code(

Delete the current message

ctx.delete_message

Delete specific message by ID

ctx.delete_message(12345)

Delete with options

ctx.delete_message(12345)  # Telegram automatically handles permissions
)

-note(Can delete bot's messages and user messages in some cases)

4). **ctx.forward_message(from_chat_id, message_id, options)

Purpose: Forward a message from any chat

-code(

Forward message from another chat

ctx.forward_message(-100123456789, 42)

Forward with options

ctx.forward_message(-100123456789, 42, disable_notification: true)
)

-note(Use negative IDs for groups/channels: -100 for supergroups)

5). **ctx.copy_message(from_chat_id, message_id, options)

Purpose: Copy a message (like forward but appears as sent by bot)

-code(
ctx.copy_message(-100123456789, 42)
ctx.copy_message("@channelusername", 42, caption: "Copied! 📋")
)

🖼️ MEDIA MESSAGES

6). **ctx.photo(photo, caption: nil, options)

Purpose: Send a photo

-code(

Send from URL

ctx.photo("https://example.com/image.jpg")

Send from file

ctx.photo(File.open("photo.jpg"), caption: "Nice photo! 📸")

Send with options

ctx.photo("image.jpg", caption: "Sunset", has_spoiler: true)
)

7). **ctx.document(document, caption: nil, options)

Purpose: Send any document/file

-code(
ctx.document("report.pdf", caption: "Monthly Report 📄")
ctx.document(File.open("data.zip"), filename: "backup.zip")
)

8). **ctx.audio(audio, caption: nil, options)

Purpose: Send audio file

-code(
ctx.audio("song.mp3", caption: "My favorite song 🎵", performer: "Artist")
ctx.audio("podcast.mp3", title: "Tech Talk", duration: 3600)
)

9). **ctx.video(video, caption: nil, options)

Purpose: Send video file

-code(
ctx.video("demo.mp4", caption: "Tutorial 📹", supports_streaming: true)
ctx.video("movie.mp4", width: 1920, height: 1080, duration: 120)
)

10). **ctx.voice(voice, caption: nil, options)

Purpose: Send voice message

-code(
ctx.voice("message.ogg", caption: "Voice message 🎤")
ctx.voice(File.open("audio.ogg"), duration: 30)
)

11). **ctx.sticker(sticker, options)

Purpose: Send sticker

-code(
ctx.sticker("CAACAgIAAxkBAAIB..."  # Sticker file_id
ctx.sticker("👍")  # Emoji sticker
)

12). **ctx.video_note(video_note, options)

Purpose: Send circular video message

-code(
ctx.video_note("video_note.mp4", length: 360, duration: 30)
)

-note(Video notes are always circular and up to 1 minute)

13). **ctx.location(latitude, longitude, options)

Purpose: Send location

-code(
ctx.location(40.7128, -74.0060)  # New York
ctx.location(51.5074, -0.1278, live_period: 3600)  # London with live location
)

14). **ctx.venue(latitude, longitude, title, address, options)

Purpose: Send venue info

-code(
ctx.venue(
40.7589, -73.9851,
"Times Square",
"Manhattan, NY 10036",
foursquare_id: "4b2c..."
)
)

15). **ctx.contact(phone_number, first_name, options)

Purpose: Send contact card

-code(
ctx.contact("+1234567890", "John", last_name: "Doe")
ctx.contact("+0987654321", "Jane", vcard: "VCARD_DATA...")
)

⌨️ CHAT ACTIONS

16). **ctx.send_chat_action(action, options)

Purpose: Show chat action (typing, uploading, etc.)

-code(
ctx.send_chat_action('typing')
ctx.send_chat_action('upload_photo')
ctx.send_chat_action('record_video')
)

17). ctx.typing(options)**

Purpose: Show typing indicator (convenience method)

-code(
ctx.typing

Equivalent to: ctx.send_chat_action('typing')

)

18). ctx.uploading_photo(options)**

Purpose: Show photo upload indicator

-code(
ctx.uploading_photo

Do some processing...

sleep 2
ctx.photo("image.jpg")
)

