🔄 CALLBACK QUERIES

28). **ctx.answer_callback_query(text: nil, show_alert: false, options)

Purpose: Answer a callback query (button click)

-code(
ctx.answer_callback_query(text: "Clicked! ✅")
ctx.answer_callback_query(text: "Error!", show_alert: true)
)

-note(Required for all callback queries to remove loading state)

29). **ctx.edit_message_text(text, options) (for callbacks)

Purpose: Edit message that contained inline keyboard

-code(

After button click, update message

ctx.answer_callback_query(text: "Processing...")
ctx.edit_message_text("You selected: #{ctx.data}")
)

30). **ctx.edit_message_caption(caption, options)

31). **ctx.edit_message_reply_markup(reply_markup, options)

⌨️ KEYBOARDS & MARKUP

32). ctx.keyboard(&block)

Purpose: Create reply keyboard builder

-code(
keyboard = ctx.keyboard do
row "Button 1", "Button 2"
row "Contact", request_contact: true
row "Location", request_location: true
end

ctx.reply("Choose:", reply_markup: keyboard)
)

33). ctx.inline_keyboard(&block)

Purpose: Create inline keyboard builder

-code(
keyboard = ctx.inline_keyboard do
row { button "Option 1", callback_data: "opt1" }
row { button "Open URL", url: "https://example.com" }
row { button "Switch Inline", switch_inline_query: "query" }
end

ctx.reply("Select:", reply_markup: keyboard)
)

34). **ctx.reply_with_keyboard(text, keyboard_markup, options)

Purpose: Send message with keyboard (convenience)

-code(
keyboard = ctx.keyboard { row "Yes", "No" }
ctx.reply_with_keyboard("Continue?", keyboard)
)

35). **ctx.reply_with_inline_keyboard(text, inline_markup, options)

36). **ctx.remove_keyboard(text = nil, options)

Purpose: Remove reply keyboard

-code(
ctx.remove_keyboard("Keyboard removed!")

or just remove without message

ctx.remove_keyboard
)

37). **ctx.force_reply(text = nil, options)

Purpose: Force user to reply to message

-code(
ctx.force_reply("Please reply to this message...")
)

👥 CHAT MANAGEMENT

38). ctx.get_chat(options)**

Purpose: Get information about a chat

-code(
chat = ctx.get_chat
ctx.reply("Chat title: #{chat.title}")
ctx.reply("Members: #{ctx.get_chat_members_count}")
)

39). ctx.get_chat_administrators(options)**

Purpose: Get list of chat administrators

-code(
admins = ctx.get_chat_administrators
admins.each do |admin|
ctx.reply("Admin: #{admin.user.first_name}")
end
)

40). **ctx.get_chat_member(user_id, options)

41). ctx.get_chat_members_count(options)**

42). ctx.leave_chat(options)**

43). **ctx.pin_message(message_id, options)

Purpose: Pin message in chat

-code(
ctx.pin_message(ctx.message.message_id)
ctx.pin_message(123, disable_notification: true)
)

44). **ctx.unpin_message(message_id = nil, options)

45). ctx.unpin_all_messages(options)**

46). **ctx.set_chat_title(title, options)

47). **ctx.set_chat_description(description, options)

48). **ctx.set_chat_photo(photo, options)

49). ctx.delete_chat_photo(options)**

50). **ctx.kick_chat_member(user_id, options)

Purpose: Kick/ban user from chat

-code(
ctx.kick_chat_member(123456789)
ctx.kick_chat_member(123456789, until_date: Time.now + 3600)  # Ban for 1 hour
)

-warning(Requires admin permissions in the chat)

51). **ctx.ban_chat_member(user_id, options)

52). **ctx.unban_chat_member(user_id, options)

53). **ctx.restrict_chat_member(user_id, options)

Purpose: Restrict user permissions

-code(
ctx.restrict_chat_member(
123456789,
can_send_messages: false,
can_send_media_messages: false
)
)

54). **ctx.promote_chat_member(user_id, options)

Purpose: Promote user to administrator

-code(
ctx.promote_chat_member(
123456789,
can_manage_chat: true,
can_delete_messages: true
)
)

55). **ctx.set_chat_administrator_custom_title(user_id, title, options)

🔗 INVITE LINKS

56). ctx.export_chat_invite_link(options)**

57). ctx.create_chat_invite_link(options)**

Purpose: Create new invite link

-code(
invite = ctx.create_chat_invite_link(
name: "VIP Access",
expire_date: Time.now + 604800,  # 7 days
member_limit: 10
)
ctx.reply("Invite link: #{invite.invite_link}")
)

58). **ctx.edit_chat_invite_link(invite_link, options)

59). **ctx.revoke_chat_invite_link(invite_link, options)

🎬 SCENE SYSTEM

60). **ctx.enter_scene(scene_name, options)

Purpose: Enter a conversation scene

-code(
ctx.enter_scene(:onboarding)
ctx.enter_scene(:auth, step: :password)
)

61). ctx.leave_scene(options)**

Purpose: Exit current scene

-code(
ctx.leave_scene
ctx.leave_scene(save_data: true)
)

62). ctx.current_scene

Purpose: Get current scene object

-code(
scene = ctx.current_scene
if scene
ctx.reply("In scene: #{scene.id}, step: #{scene.current_step(ctx)}")
end
)

📊 ACCESSORS & HELPERS

63). ctx.message

Purpose: Get the Message object

-code(
if ctx.message
ctx.reply("Message ID: #{ctx.message.message_id}")
ctx.reply("From: #{ctx.message.from.first_name}")
end
)

64). ctx.callback_query

65). ctx.inline_query

66). ctx.from

Purpose: Get user who sent the update

-code(
user = ctx.from
ctx.reply("Hello #{user.first_name}!")
ctx.reply("Your ID: #{user.id}")
ctx.reply("Username: @#{user.username}") if user.username
)

67). ctx.chat

Purpose: Get chat where update came from

-code(
chat = ctx.chat
ctx.reply("Chat type: #{chat.type}")
ctx.reply("Chat ID: #{chat.id}")
ctx.reply("Title: #{chat.title}") if chat.title
)

68). ctx.user_id

Purpose: Shortcut for ctx.from.id

-code(

Instead of:

user_id = ctx.from.id

Use:

user_id = ctx.user_id
)

69). ctx.chat_id

Purpose: Shortcut for ctx.chat.id

70). ctx.text

Purpose: Get message text

-code(
if ctx.text
ctx.reply("You said: #{ctx.text}")
end
)

71). ctx.caption

72). ctx.data

Purpose: Get callback query data

-code(
if ctx.data
ctx.reply("Button data: #{ctx.data}")
ctx.answer_callback_query(text: "Received: #{ctx.data}")
end
)

73). ctx.query

Purpose: Get inline query text

74). ctx.command?

Purpose: Check if message is a command

-code(
if ctx.command?
ctx.reply("That's a command!")
else
ctx.reply("That's not a command.")
end
)

75). ctx.command_name

Purpose: Get command name without slash

-code(
if ctx.command?
ctx.reply("Command: #{ctx.command_name}")

/start → "start"

/help@bot → "help"

end
)

76). ctx.command_args

Purpose: Get command arguments

-code(

For: /search ruby programming

if ctx.command? && ctx.command_name == "search"
query = ctx.command_args  # "ruby programming"
ctx.reply("Searching for: #{query}")
end
)

77). ctx.match

Purpose: Get regex match data from hears() handler

-code(
bot.hears(/hello (\w+)/) do |ctx|
name = ctx.match[1]  # Captured group
ctx.reply("Hello #{name}!")
end
)

78). ctx.session

Purpose: Access user session data

-code(

Store data

ctx.session[:counter] = (ctx.session[:counter] || 0) + 1

Retrieve data

count = ctx.session[:counter]
ctx.reply("You've visited #{count} times")
)

79). ctx.state

Purpose: Temporary state for current handler

-code(
ctx.state[:processing] = true

... do work ...

ctx.state.delete(:processing)
)

80). ctx.api

Purpose: Direct access to API client

-code(

Make raw API call

response = ctx.api.call!('getMe')
ctx.reply("Bot name: #{response['result']['first_name']}")
)

81). ctx.logger

Purpose: Access logger instance

-code(
ctx.logger.info("Processing update from #{ctx.user_id}")
ctx.logger.error("Something went wrong!") if error
)

82). ctx.update

Purpose: Raw update object

-code(
update_id = ctx.update.update_id
update_type = ctx.update.type
ctx.logger.debug("Update ##{update_id}, type: #{update_type}")
)

83). ctx.with_typing(&block)

Purpose: Show typing indicator while executing block

-code(
ctx.with_typing do

Long processing...

sleep 3
ctx.reply("Done! ✅")
end
)

